Volkswagen Group said on Wednesday that VW and its 11 subsidiary brands sold 10.7 million vehicles in 2017, a 4.3 percent increase on the previous year. The growth means that the company has likely overtaken its nearest rival to become the world's largest car producer for the year. Read more: VW teams up with Silicon Valley firm to produce self-driving cars The figures — which include sales of Porsche, Audi, Skoda and Seat among other brands — were highly anticipated, coming in the wake of the emissions cheating scandal that rocked the German automaker for the past two years. Send  Facebook   Twitter   Google+   Whatsapp   
